@node Introduction
@chapter Introduction
@cindex introduction
This manual describes how to install and use @value{PACKAGE}, an Emacs
package for working with @cite{Graphviz} DOT-format files.  The
features of this package help you to create @file{.dot} or @file{.gv}
files using syntax compatible with the separate @cite{Graphviz} package
and use @cite{Graphviz} to convert these files to diagrams.

@pindex Graphiz
@cite{Graphviz} is a set of open source graph visualization tools
created by @acronym{AT&T} Labs Research.  A @emph{graph} is a way of
representing information as a network of connected @emph{nodes} and
@emph{edges}. @cite{Graphviz} is documented at
@url{http://graphviz.org}.

@pindex Emacs
The powerful text editor, Emacs, was created in 1976 by Richard Stallman,
is highly extensible and has a large ecosystem of extensions like this one
one created over 40 years.  @acronym{GNU} Emacs is documented at
@uref{https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/}.

